cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

This paper deals with convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and their application in computer vision and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel activation scheme and analyzes its theoretical properties, which falls under the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the improvement in recognition performance, which can be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper uses datasets such as CIFAR-10/100 and ImageNet, which are commonly used in the sub-category of cs.MM (Multimedia).
